29/07/2004
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- General Richard B. 
Myers, chairman of the US Joint Chiefs of Staff, arrived on a two-day visit to Sofia Wednesday (28 July). 
He is to discuss the possible relocation of US military bases to Bulgaria with President Georgi Parvanov, Prime Minister Simeon Saxe-Coburg and Chief of Army General Staff General Nikola Kolev.
In other news, the government is expected to decide Thursday to allocate an additional 95,000 euros to the Bulgarian Police Academy for training Iraqi security officers. 
The training will cover human rights protection, public order and personal protection, and other areas. 
(24 Chasa - 29/07/04; Mediapool, news.bg - 28/07/04)
